<p>I have mentioned his credulity which will be exemplified in what follows.  He has also, a little trick of repeating little parenthetical sentences ad lib, forgetting that the rather unimportant point referred to be made is in danger of being unduly brought forward.  Thus in referring to his wife he hardly mentions her in connection with any episode but <strike>which</strike> he adds "My fianc&eacute;e which she was then" or "of course she was my fianc&eacute;e at that time", or "my wife or fianc&eacute;e as she then was".</p>
<p>(continued in No. 9)</p>
